definition: to close by coming together (like the lips of a wound, the doors of an elevator, the walls of a channel)/to close by connecting in a loop (like a circuit)/closed-loop
cecum (start of the colon, linking it to small intestine)
latch/bolt (to lock a door or window)
to pull out/to pull a lever
to restore sb or sth to its original position/to regain the throne/to reset (a dislocated joint, an electronic device etc)/reset
